items.text: tailing in again, but this was a bit quicker and Tamim was too late on the flick. Leading edge rolls to point

items.text: got him! This was on the pads again and Tamim flicked it well, but Holder at short midwicket plucks it out, holding it low to his right. Moved very quickly and very agilely - had to because the ball was travelling. Smart take by the captain
items.shortText: Gabriel to Tamim Iqbal, OUT

dismissal.text: Tamim Iqbal c Holder b Gabriel 80 (158m 116b 7x4 0x6) SR: 68.96

items.preText: Jai: "West Indies should try to eke out a couple of dry overs and see if panic sets in. The only way they can win this (or entertain thoughts of winning) is by instilling some pressure." - and it's the perfect time to do it after a wicket
items.text: oooh that one popped in the air, but no one at short fine leg. Jagged in from a length and bounced a bit more than he expected, and he gets a glove to it while trying to tickle it fine.

items.preText: Despite that wicket, Bangladesh are in the comfortable position of needing just 64 runs from 13 overs. They have eight wickets in hand, so should be still strong favourites
